{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, ArguLens (Wang et al., 2020) utilizes a domain-specific structure by imposing an argumentation-enhanced representation, breaking the user text into argumentation components and standpoints.",
    "Despite these valuable contributions, none of the existing systems combine adaptive instruction with a comparison example that could leverage the potential of examplebased learning.",
    "To study the effect of personalized example-based feedback on learners' writing performance, revision behavior, and learning experience, we designed RELEX (REcipe Learning through EXamples).",
    "The primary purpose of RELEX is to facilitate procedural writing by providing students with tailored examples, accompanied by relevant annotations and reflective prompts.",
    "The tool aims to address three key aspects of procedural writing: (a) the organization and structure of texts, (b) the provision of requisite details for enhanced clarity, and (c) the appropriate utilization of specific vocabulary."
  ]
}